# Excel Reporting Rules

Excel output must be professional, readable and useful for CA firms.

The target users are CAs, auditors, accountants and finance teams.

Do not create raw data dumps unless explicitly requested as a debug export.

---

## Workbook Metadata

Every workbook should include metadata such as:

- Company name
- Report name
- Period
- Generated timestamp
- Source connection
- Source Tally company
- Extraction status
- Generated by TallyMCP Pro
- Notes or limitations, where applicable

---

## Standard Workbook Structure

For normal reports, prefer:

```text
Summary
Data
Exceptions
Mapping
Notes
Extraction Log
```

Use only relevant sheets. Do not add empty sheets unnecessarily.

For financial statements, prefer:

```text
Cover
Balance Sheet
Profit and Loss
Cash Flow
Notes to Accounts
Ledger Mapping
Review Points
Extraction Log
```

For write templates, prefer:

```text
Instructions
Data Entry
Master Reference
Tax Ledger Reference
Validation Rules
Examples
Errors
Posting Status
```

For audit/review reports, prefer:

```text
Executive Summary
Risk Summary
Findings
Voucher Exceptions
Ledger Exceptions
Suggested Procedures
Evidence Required
Data
Extraction Log
```

---

## Formatting Rules

Use consistent formatting:

- Clear title at top
- Company name below title
- Period below company name
- Generated timestamp
- Bold header rows
- Freeze panes
- Auto filter
- Proper column widths
- Wrapped text where required
- Date format: `dd-mmm-yyyy`
- Amount format suitable for Indian accounting users
- Negative values should be easy to identify
- Total and subtotal rows should be clearly visible
- Avoid unnecessary merged cells
- Avoid excessive colors
- Avoid visually cluttered sheets

---

## Number Format Rules

Use accounting-friendly number formatting.

Recommended amount formats:

```text
#,##,##0.00
#,##,##0.00;(#,##,##0.00)
```

For quantity:

```text
#,##,##0.000
```

For percentage:

```text
0.00%
```

For dates:

```text
dd-mmm-yyyy
```

Do not store numbers as text unless unavoidable.

Do not store dates as plain strings if proper date values can be used.

---

## Sheet Naming Rules

Sheet names should be short and readable.

Good:

```text
Summary
Data
Exceptions
Ledger Mapping
Extraction Log
```

Bad:

```text
Sheet1
RawDumpFinal2
VeryLongSheetNameThatExcelMayReject
```

Excel sheet names must not exceed Excel limits.

Avoid invalid characters in sheet names.

---

## Report Output Rules

Every report output should include:

- Summary view
- Detailed data view
- Exception view, where applicable
- Extraction log

The extraction log should include:

- Report ID
- Company
- Period
- Tally host/port or connection name
- Start time
- End time
- Status
- Error message if failed

---

## Financial Statement Rules

Financial statement workbooks should be professional enough to share internally with management or audit teams.

Include:

- Balance Sheet
- Statement of Profit and Loss
- Cash Flow Statement, where available
- Notes to Accounts placeholder
- Ledger-to-financial-statement mapping
- Review points
- Previous period comparison where available

Do not claim final statutory compliance without professional review.

Use phrases such as:

```text
Draft financial statement format
Requires professional review
Mapping to be confirmed by user
```

---

## Template Workbook Rules

Write templates must be easy for accountants to fill.

Every write template should include:

- Instructions sheet
- Data entry sheet
- Required fields clearly marked
- Dropdown/reference values where practical
- Master reference sheet
- Example rows
- Validation rules
- Error/status output

Do not expect the user to know internal Tally XML fields.

Use accounting-friendly column names.

Example good column names:

```text
Voucher Date
Voucher Type
Party Ledger
Sales Ledger
Invoice Number
Item Name
Quantity
Rate
Taxable Value
CGST
SGST
IGST
Narration
```

Avoid technical internal names in user-facing templates unless needed.

---

## Error Workbook Rules

When validation fails, generate an error workbook.

The error workbook should include:

- Original row number
- Field name
- Entered value
- Error message
- Suggested correction
- Severity
- Whether posting is blocked

Severity values:

```text
Error
Warning
Info
```

Errors block posting.

Warnings require review but may not block posting.

Info is advisory.

---

## Large Data Rules

For large exports:

- Avoid keeping unnecessary duplicate data in memory
- Use streaming write where practical
- Split very large reports into multiple sheets if needed
- Include summary sheet first
- Clearly mention if data was truncated or paginated
- Never silently omit records

---

## Professional Presentation Rules

Excel output should look like a CA firm generated it, not a developer dump.

Prioritize:

- Readability
- Auditability
- Traceability
- Clean structure
- Clear totals
- Clear exceptions
- Practical review flow

Always keep raw data available in a separate sheet when formatted summaries are generated.
